ys middle-aged women are underestimated, even by themselves.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aMothers and daughtersvFiction. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  aContemporary fiction.  aadult children.  aaging.  agrief.  agrieving.  aliterary fiction.  aloss.  alost children.  amiddle-age.  amotherhood.  aparenting.  areconnection.  arecovery.  areinvention.  arelationship building.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2024z978311140848440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781773854830?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781773854830423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781773854830/original  a978-3-11-140848-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2024b2024  aGBV-deGruyter-alles